Description: Squat calcite canopic jar: Duamutef; four columns of Hieroglyphic text on the body.
Curator's comments: The jar formed part of a set with EA 36536, EA 36537 and EA 36539. The source of the group, 'Sm', is noted only on the Birch Slip for EA 36539 [E.S. 639], but all four jars are inscribed with the same name and they are listed as a set in the 3-volume MS catalogue of the Sams Collection (AES archive).
